{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn about how to set up your project with the new authentication flow changes."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"With the release of 0.26.0 comes a new migration flow for ATProtoKit developers. This change is fairly small, but this article will still cover what to expect in order to clear any confusion.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Authentication Flow","anchor":"Authentication-Flow","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Previously, when you wanted to authenticate to an AT Protocol service, you used an initializer from ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":", which contained the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"handle"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"password"},{"type":"text","text":" parameters. Then, you would use ATProtocolConfiguration.authenticate(authenticationFactorToken:) and passed the instance to the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoKit"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration(handle: example.bsky.social, password: hunter2)","","Task {","    do {","        \/\/ You can put it in here…","        try await config.authenticate()","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Or here…","        try await config.authenticate()","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With version 0.26, this has been changed slightly:"}]},{"code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration()","","Task {","    do {","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Enter the handle and password in here.","        try await config.authenticate(","            handle: example.bsky.social,","            password: hunter2","        )","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Here are the changes being made:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"’s initializer no longer takes the "},{"code":"handle","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"password","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" parameters: now, "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is responsible."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This is the only external change. However, more has been made internally:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSession","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is no longer stored inside of "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":": now, a new "},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" named "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSessionRegistry","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" holds all instances of the "},{"code":"struct","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"code":"UUID","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" value has been added to the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". This value is linked to all objects that are related to the session. This is part of the new initializer for "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":", named "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":" now closely follows "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":". In fact, the following methods are no longer stored in the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"text":", but have moved to default implementations of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/getSession()","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/refreshSession()","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/deleteSession()","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}]}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A new "},{"code":"protocol","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", named "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", will now manage the management of the password, access token, and refresh token. An "},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", named "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is available for applications running on Apple’s platforms."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"`SessionConfiguration`","anchor":"SessionConfiguration"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As mentioned previously, "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":" now has default configurations for each of the required methods. It is also "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sendable"},{"type":"text","text":" and requires a "},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to conform to it. The default implementation assumes you’re using an App Password to authenticate by default, but you’re able to create new implementations for your own conforming ","type":"text"},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Furthermore, the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" method handles Two-Factor Authentication by waiting on ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeStream"},{"text":" after the server requests a code. Pass the code back through ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/receiveCodeFromUser(_:)"},{"text":". The same ","type":"text"},{"code":"AsyncStream","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"-related properties, named ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeContinuation"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeStream"},{"text":", can also support custom OAuth flows.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Auto-managing the Keychain","anchor":"Auto-managing-the-Keychain"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"As mentioned earlier, a new ","type":"text"},{"code":"protocol","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" have been made: ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain"},{"text":" respectively. This manages the keychain items for the password and refresh token, as well as storing the access token in-memory.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The access token is being stored in-memory due to how frequently the token expires."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain"},{"type":"text","text":" conforms to "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" and is the default object used for Apple platforms. It’s also the default object used when initializing with "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":". However, you’re free to create your own implementation if it doesn’t suit your needs."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"At this time, Linux and Windows developers will need to implement their own "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":" to achieve the same effect. However, default "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"type":"text","text":"s for those platforms will be created at a later date."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"article","sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/0210AuthFlowChange"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/atprotokit\/0210authflowchange"]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"ATProtoKit"}],"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","title":"0.21 to 0.26 Authentication Flow Migration"},"references":{"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/SecureKeychainProtocol":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/atprotokit\/securekeychainprotocol","abstract":[{"text":"A protocol for managing the keychain in an AT Protcol account.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SecureKeychainProtocol"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SecureKeychainProtocol"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","title":"SecureKeychainProtocol"},"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/SessionConfiguration/codeContinuation":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/atprotokit\/sessionconfiguration\/codecontinuation","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The continuation used to yield new user input into the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"codeStream"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"codeContinuation","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AsyncStream","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScS","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"String","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">.","kind":"text"},{"text":"Continuation","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScS12ContinuationV","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeContinuation","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","title":"codeContinuation","required":true},"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/SessionConfiguration/receiveCodeFromUser(_:)":{"title":"receiveCodeFromUser(_:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"receiveCodeFromUser","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"String","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","defaultImplementations":1,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/receiveCodeFromUser(_:)","url":"\/documentation\/atprotokit\/sessionconfiguration\/receivecodefromuser(_:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Takes the Two-Factor Authentication code inputted from the user."}],"required":true,"role":"symbol"},"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/ATProtocolConfiguration/init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)":{"kind":"symbol","type":"